<DOC><DOCNO> AP900714-0117 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-14-90 1853EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Mauritania-Crash     07-14 0095</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Mauritania-Crash,0097</SECOND><HEAD>Bus Accident Kills 23 People in Mauritania</HEAD><DATELINE>NOUAKCHOTT, Mauritania (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A bus accident blamed on poor roadconditions killed 23 people and injured 29 in this northwestAfrican country, an official report said Saturday.   The accident Friday involved a bus carrying about 100 peoplefrom the eastern city of Nema to the capital, Nouakchott, theMauritanian News Agency said.   The agency blamed the accident on the poor condition ofMauritania's roads, most of which badly need repair. It did not saywhether any other vehicles were involved or provide other details.</TEXT></DOC>